        <section class="experience">
          <h2>Experience</h2>

          <ol role="list" class="flow">
            <li>
              <article class="job flow">
                <header>
                  <span class="role">UX Engineer</span>
                  <span class="employer"
                    ><a href="https://talis.com">Talis Education Ltd</a></span
                  >
                  <span class="details">May 2021–May 2023, Remote</span>
                </header>
                <ul class="flow">
                  <li>
                    Led and developed accessibility strategy across Talis, which
                    resulted in a 90% reduction in WCAG issues across our two
                    SaaS products.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Designed and prototyped functionality allowing the discovery
                    and creation of annotations for a video player. This had
                    previously been impossible for keyboard and assistive
                    technology users.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Performed user research, created wireframes, and prototyped
                    UI components for a React-based rewrite of a collaborative
                    teaching and learning product.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Facilitated group and one-to-one discovery sessions with
                    customers; used unmoderated usability testing tools in order
                    to measure the success of proposed solutions.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Used analytics to guide design decisions and measure the
                    success of design initiatives.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Authored and maintained the Talis design system which
                    ensured product, engineering, and design teams could move
                    straight to solving the more complex design problems.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Coached peers on design and engineering teams, helping them
                    improve their understanding of accessibility and
                    user-centred design, while promoting empathy with our
                    student, academic, and library audiences.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </article>
            </li>
            <li>
              <article class="job flow">
                <header>
                  <span class="role">Developer</span>
                  <span class="employer"
                    ><a href="https://talis.com">Talis Education Ltd</a></span
                  >
                  <span class="details">June 2015–May 2021, Remote</span>
                </header>
                <ul class="flow">
                  <li>
                    Designed and built an Angular SPA to consolidate theming
                    options for 100+ institutions, reducing complexity for Talis
                    services team and customers, while resolving a number of
                    outstanding accessibility issues.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Delivered a UI refresh of Aspire, a reading list and
                    copyright clearance product in first six months.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Core contributor towards an Angular SPA replacement for
                    Talis&apos; legacy PHP application.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Implemented a visual refresh of Elevate, a teaching and
                    learning product, in order to support a product-led growth
                    initiative.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Built and maintained WordPress theme for Talis marketing
                    team to boost SEO and drive promotion.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </article>
            </li>
            <li>
              <article class="job flow">
